 {"id":"bd-159","title":"Implement StatsRenderer for beautiful metrics display","description":"## Purpose and Rationale

Create a renderer that transforms ServerStats snapshots into beautiful rich_rust output - tables, panels, and formatted text that looks premium in the terminal.

## Background

Raw metrics are useful but not engaging. The StatsRenderer transforms cold numbers into a visually appealing dashboard-style display using rich_rust's Table, Panel, and styled text capabilities. This is what makes the server feel polished.

## Technical Specification

### Core Structure

```rust
// crates/fastmcp-console/src/stats/renderer.rs

use rich_rust::{Table, Panel, Column, JustifyMethod, Style};
use crate::console::FastMcpConsole;
use crate::theme::FastMcpTheme;
use crate::context::DisplayContext;
use super::StatsSnapshot;

/// Renders server statistics in various formats
pub struct StatsRenderer {
    theme: FastMcpTheme,
    context: DisplayContext,
}

impl StatsRenderer {
    pub fn new(theme: FastMcpTheme, context: DisplayContext) -> Self {
        Self { theme, context }
    }

    /// Render a full statistics panel
    pub fn render_panel(&self, stats: &StatsSnapshot, console: &FastMcpConsole) {
        if !self.context.should_use_rich() {
            self.render_plain(stats, console);
            return;
        }

        let content = self.build_stats_content(stats);
        let panel = Panel::from_text(&content)
            .title("Server Statistics")
            .width(60)
            .style(self.theme.panel_border_style());

        console.print_renderable(&panel);
    }

    /// Render as a compact table
    pub fn render_table(&self, stats: &StatsSnapshot, console: &FastMcpConsole) {
        if !self.context.should_use_rich() {
            self.render_plain(stats, console);
            return;
        }

        let mut table = Table::new()
            .title("Runtime Metrics")
            .with_column(Column::new("Metric").style(self.theme.dim_style()))
            .with_column(Column::new("Value").justify(JustifyMethod::Right));

        // Uptime with formatted duration
        table.add_row_cells(["Uptime", &self.format_duration(stats.uptime)]);

        // Request counts
        table.add_row_cells(["Total Requests", &stats.total_requests.to_string()]);
        table.add_row_cells([
            "Success Rate",
            &self.format_percentage(stats.successful_requests, stats.total_requests)
        ]);

        // Breakdown by type
        table.add_row_cells(["  Tool Calls", &stats.tool_calls.to_string()]);
        table.add_row_cells(["  Resource Reads", &stats.resource_reads.to_string()]);
        table.add_row_cells(["  Prompt Gets", &stats.prompt_gets.to_string()]);

        // Latency
        table.add_row_cells(["Avg Latency", &self.format_latency(stats.avg_latency)]);
        table.add_row_cells(["Max Latency", &self.format_latency(stats.max_latency)]);

        // Connections
        table.add_row_cells(["Active Connections", &stats.active_connections.to_string()]);

        // Data transfer
        table.add_row_cells(["Data Received", &self.format_bytes(stats.bytes_received)]);
        table.add_row_cells(["Data Sent", &self.format_bytes(stats.bytes_sent)]);

        console.print_renderable(&table);
    }

    /// Render a compact one-line summary
    pub fn render_oneline(&self, stats: &StatsSnapshot, console: &FastMcpConsole) {
        let line = if self.context.should_use_rich() {
            format!(
                "[dim]⏱[/] {} [dim]│[/] [cyan]{}[/] reqs [dim]│[/] [green]{:.1}%[/] ok [dim]│[/] [yellow]{}[/] avg",
                self.format_duration(stats.uptime),
                stats.total_requests,
                self.success_rate(stats) * 100.0,
                self.format_latency(stats.avg_latency)
            )
        } else {
            format!(
                "Uptime: {} | Requests: {} | Success: {:.1}% | Avg latency: {}",
                self.format_duration(stats.uptime),
                stats.total_requests,
                self.success_rate(stats) * 100.0,
                self.format_latency(stats.avg_latency)
            )
        };

        console.print(&line);
    }

    // Helper methods

    fn format_duration(&self, d: Duration) -> String {
        let secs = d.as_secs();
        if secs < 60 {
            format!("{}s", secs)
        } else if secs < 3600 {
            format!("{}m {}s", secs / 60, secs % 60)
        } else {
            format!("{}h {}m", secs / 3600, (secs % 3600) / 60)
        }
    }

    fn format_latency(&self, d: Duration) -> String {
        let micros = d.as_micros();
        if micros < 1000 {
            format!("{}μs", micros)
        } else if micros < 1_000_000 {
            format!("{:.1}ms", micros as f64 / 1000.0)
        } else {
            format!("{:.2}s", micros as f64 / 1_000_000.0)
        }
    }

    fn format_bytes(&self, bytes: u64) -> String {
        const KB: u64 = 1024;
        const MB: u64 = KB * 1024;
        const GB: u64 = MB * 1024;

        if bytes < KB {
            format!("{} B", bytes)
        } else if bytes < MB {
            format!("{:.1} KB", bytes as f64 / KB as f64)
        } else if bytes < GB {
            format!("{:.1} MB", bytes as f64 / MB as f64)
        } else {
            format!("{:.2} GB", bytes as f64 / GB as f64)
        }
    }

    fn format_percentage(&self, part: u64, total: u64) -> String {
        if total == 0 {
            "N/A".to_string()
        } else {
            format!("{:.1}%", (part as f64 / total as f64) * 100.0)
        }
    }

    fn success_rate(&self, stats: &StatsSnapshot) -> f64 {
        if stats.total_requests == 0 {
            1.0
        } else {
            stats.successful_requests as f64 / stats.total_requests as f64
        }
    }

    fn render_plain(&self, stats: &StatsSnapshot, console: &FastMcpConsole) {
        console.print(&format!("=== Server Statistics ==="));
        console.print(&format!("Uptime: {}", self.format_duration(stats.uptime)));
        console.print(&format!("Requests: {} total, {} successful, {} failed",
            stats.total_requests, stats.successful_requests, stats.failed_requests));
        console.print(&format!("Latency: {} avg, {} max",
            self.format_latency(stats.avg_latency), self.format_latency(stats.max_latency)));
    }
}
```

## Implementation Steps

1. Create stats/renderer.rs in crates/fastmcp-console/src/
2. Implement render_panel() with full statistics
3. Implement render_table() for compact table view
4. Implement render_oneline() for status bar style
5. Add all formatting helper methods
6. Implement plain-text fallback
7. Add visual tests (snapshot tests)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Panel rendering shows all key metrics
- [ ] Table rendering is properly aligned
- [ ] One-line summary is concise and readable
- [ ] All durations format correctly (s/m/h)
- [ ] All byte sizes format correctly (B/KB/MB/GB)
- [ ] Percentages handle edge cases (0 requests)
- [ ] Plain-text fallback is functional
- [ ] Colors follow theme consistently

## Visual Example (Rich Mode)

```
